				<div class="box">
			<h3>Editorial comment</h3>
			<p>A critical factor in future patterns of ACP-EU sugar trade will be the routes to market chosen by individual ACP suppliers. British Sugar’s joint venture with Illovo, with which other ACP sugar exporting entities are being invited to become associated, will offer a new route to EU markets once EU import licence allocation procedures are reformed. This will offer both a route for raw sugar export to sister companies of British Sugar elsewhere in Europe (e.g. the Ebro refinery in Spain) and also potentially new routes for the export of value-added sugars and even final-consumption sugars to a wide variety of consumers across Europe. This will throw up new challenges for ACP sugar companies in terms of strengthening their commercial negotiating capacities, as EU prices are reduced and price guarantees are progressively dismantled.</p>
		</div>
		
